{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"5055c141-4593-49c2-a649-b88f29617998","content":"Two things change with xUnit v3 + MTP:\n\n**1. Filter syntax** — MTP doesn't use VSTest's `--filter`. Instead the test executable accepts `--filter` directly, but the operators differ:\n\n| VSTest (v2) | MTP (v3) |\n|---|---|\n| `~` (contains) | `~=` |\n| `&` (and) | `&` (same) |\n| `Category` | `trait:Category` |\n\n**2. Invocation** — With `UseMicrosoftTestingPlatformRunner`, use `dotnet run` or invoke the built executable, not `dotnet test`:\n\n```bash\ndotnet run --project TestProject.csproj -- \\\n  --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~=IntegrationTests&trait:Category=Smoke\"\n```\n\nOr if you prefer `dotnet test` (which forwards to MTP):\n\n```bash\ndotnet test TestProject.csproj -- \\\n  --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~=IntegrationTests&trait:Category=Smoke\"\n```\n\nNote the `--` separator — everything after it is passed to MTP.\n\n**Key differences from your old command:**\n- `~` → `~=` (contains operator)\n- `Category=Smoke` → `trait:Category=Smoke` (traits are prefixed with `trait:`)","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"dfae47ae-695c-462d-b371-ed3dda51995c","outputTokens":327},"id":"b1d503fe-3d1b-45ad-a725-41ab8b5023ef","timestamp":"2026-04-07T13:06:48.545Z","parentId":"9aaec34a-8475-400d-be86-d6e901bc1789"}
